messages.content:
Sir Elton,
I know that I am out of character to demand but given the circumstances, I feel insulted on my part, on my capacity and the role that I took part and on the effort I have exerted for the company. If there is an assessment on my performance, which there should be, I believe that this compensation that was given to me do not reflect my contributions. Yes, tenure-wise, I have just been with the company for over a year but please consider the role, the load and the accountabilities I carry with me. I am working on both finance and accounting role as well and the demands that these roles are asking are not easy. If for you, the increase that I got is justifiable with the nature of my work, then I rest my case. But if not, I am asking you to kindly revisit it. I am emailing you in the hopes that you will take action on my concern. If Maâam Anne cannot back me app on this matter, who else should I see help for?
